                    rdfs:subClassOf resource:SIO_000596 ;
                    dc:identifier "SIO_000598" ;
                    terms:description "A hard disk drive (HDD) is a non-volatile, random access device for digital data. It features rotating rigid platters on a motor-driven spindle within a protective enclosure. Data is magnetically read and written on the platter by read/write heads that float on a film of air above the platters."@en ;
                    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://semanticscience.org/ontology/sio.owl> ;
                    rdfs:label "hard disk drive"@en .


