                    dc:identifier "SIO_000977" ;
                    terms:description "A syllable is a verbal entity of language having one vowel sound, with or without surrounding consonants, forming the whole or a part of a word."@en ;
                    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://semanticscience.org/ontology/sio.owl> ;
                    rdfs:label "syllable"@en .


###  http://semanticscience.org/resource/SIO_000978
