                    rdfs:subClassOf resource:SIO_000091 ;
                    dc:identifier "SIO_001043" ;
                    terms:description "An experimental protocol is an action specification with respect to the design and implementation of experiments. In addition to providing a detailed set of procedures and lists of required equipment and instruments, experimental protocols often include information on safety precautions, the calculation of results and reporting standards, including statistical analysis and rules for predefining and documenting excluded data to avoid bias."@en ;
                    rdfs:isDefinedBy <http://semanticscience.org/ontology/sio.owl> ;
                    rdfs:label "experimental protocol"@en .


